events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore ran for two touchdowns and 110 yards, and Connor Shaw ran for 92 yards while playing the second half with an injured shoulder as No. 9 South Carolina rallied for a 17-13 victory against Vanderbilt to open the season Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 South Carolina holds off Vandy

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Ball State Cardinals
Southeast Missouri State Redhawks at Central Michigan Chippewas
Towson Tigers at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: Dri Archer ran a kickoff back 98 yards for a touchdown and rushed for two scores as Kent State overwhelmed Towson 41-21 Thursday night in the teams' season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kent State player runs 58 yards wrong way

events.name: Northern Colorado Bears at Utah Utes

headlines.description: John White rushed for 119 yards, Jordan Wynn threw for two touchdowns and backup quarterback Travis Wilson ran for two more scores to power Utah over Northern Colorado 41-0.
headlines.shortLinkText: White, Wynn lead Utah past Northern Colorado

headlines.description: Chandler Whitmer threw for 219 yards and Connecticut scored touchdowns on offense, defense and special teams to beat Massachusetts 37-0 Thursday night, spoiling the Minutemen's debut as a bowl subdivision program.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn spoils UMass' FBS debut with shutout

headlines.description: Johnathan Franklin rushed for 214 yards and three touchdowns as UCLA racked up 348 yards on the ground en route to a 49-24 win over Rice on Thursday night.

events.name: South Carolina State Bulldogs at Georgia State Panthers
McNeese State Cowboys at Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders

headlines.description: Cody Stroud recorded two touchdowns and McNeese State racked up 298 rushing yards as the Cowboys defeated Middle Tennessee 27-21 on the road Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FCS team McNeese St. upsets FBS Middle Tenn.

events.name: Sacramento State Hornets at New Mexico State Aggies
Southern Utah Thunderbirds at Utah State Aggies
Washington State Cougars at BYU Cougars

headlines.description: Riley Nelson threw for two touchdowns and third-string quarterback Taysom Hill added another on his first collegiate pass as Brigham Young beat Washington State 30-6 on Thursday night to spoil Mike Leach's return to coaching.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leach's return spoiled as BYU routs Wazzu

events.name: Northern Arizona Lumberjacks at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Marion Grice ran for three touchdowns, Taylor Kelly was efficient in his desert debut and Arizona State opened the Todd Graham era with a 63-6 rout over Northern Arizona Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham gets easy win in Arizona St. debut

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: MarQueis Gray threw two touchdown passes to John Rabe in overtime, and Jordan Wettstein hit a 32-yard field goal in the third extra session to lift Minnesota over UNLV 30-27 Thursday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minnesota outlasts UNLV on field goal in 3rd OT

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Louisiana Tech Bulldogs
